                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I stopped the prisoner coming out of the dock with these things; I found on him one plane, two printed books, ten yards of ribbon, and a shirt, wrapped up in a pair of trousers - he said they had been given him by a lad on board the Roslyn; I took him there, and found the ship-keeper and a boy - they said he had been sent there, and was desired to go on shore again- I took him to the office, the prosecutor appeared, and identified the property.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
